### CI Workflow Design
nightly-version runs only on main pushes (skipped on PRs — skipped != failed).
build-binary checks if nightly-version output is non-empty before injecting version.
publish-nightly runs only after build-binary and test-e2e succeed on main.
Rolling nightly release created once; assets replaced via gh release upload --clobber.

### Nightly Download URL
getBinaryDownloadUrl("nightly") reuses the same URL pattern as stable releases
but with "nightly" as the tag. The .gz download + decompression logic is fully reused.

### Version Comparison
Bun.semver.order() handles nightly-to-nightly correctly: the unix timestamp in
-dev.<ts> is a numeric pre-release identifier compared numerically.
channelChanged=true bypasses the already-up-to-date check when switching channels.

### User Flows
  # Fresh nightly install
  curl -fsSL https://cli.sentry.dev/install | bash -s -- --version nightly

  # Switch existing install to nightly
  sentry cli upgrade nightly

  # Regular update (channel persisted)
  sentry cli upgrade

  # Force re-download even if up to date
  sentry cli upgrade --force

  # Switch back to stable
  sentry cli upgrade stable
